00:28:25.690 --> 00:28:28.390
&gt;&gt; I have a question
about deaf culture.

00:28:29.660 --> 00:28:35.190
It's about the content
of deaf culture.

00:28:35.190 --> 00:28:39.730
I was trained to be a
cataloger at a GPO when I worked

00:28:39.730 --> 00:28:42.070
at GPO by a deaf cataloger.

00:28:42.070 --> 00:28:46.440
And there was no interpreting
services there at the time.

00:28:46.440 --> 00:28:53.010
And I had a wonderful experience
learning from her, and afterwards,

00:28:53.010 --> 00:28:56.110
I wondered when I was
this training so good.

00:28:56.110 --> 00:29:02.900
And I came to understand that
hearing people like to talk a lot.

00:29:02.900 --> 00:29:05.150
There's a lot of BS.

00:29:05.150 --> 00:29:09.660
And this is my question
as an outsider.

00:29:09.660 --> 00:29:12.840
And I realized that
she taught me in a way

00:29:12.840 --> 00:29:19.490
where her words were very important
and very short and concise.

00:29:19.490 --> 00:29:24.030
So my question is, as a hearing
person, if I would listen

00:29:24.030 --> 00:29:30.910
to deaf poetry, for example, or
deaf comedy, would it be something

00:29:30.910 --> 00:29:34.880
that would be more compressed
or shorter in content

00:29:34.880 --> 00:29:50.780
if you understand my question?

00:29:50.780 --> 00:29:54.680
&gt;&gt; Max Williamson: Yeah, maybe
ask it again in a different way.

00:29:54.680 --> 00:30:01.130
Yeah, if that's okay, ask it again.

00:30:01.130 --> 00:30:06.530 position:56%
&gt;&gt; My experience learning from a
deaf teacher as a hearing person was

00:30:06.530 --> 00:30:12.180
that she was very concise
and to the point.

00:30:12.180 --> 00:30:14.840
Very little BS.

00:30:16.390 --> 00:30:23.380 position:56%
And I'm wondering if I went to a
deaf cultural event like deaf comedy

00:30:23.380 --> 00:30:30.460
or deaf poetry, whether the
expression would be that same way,

00:30:30.460 --> 00:30:36.460
more concise and shorter
in terms of its content?

00:30:42.500 --> 00:30:45.620
&gt;&gt; Max Williamson: Okay, so you
think that maybe like deaf culture

00:30:45.620 --> 00:30:50.480 position:56%
and the deaf language is more
concise and to the point on its own?

00:30:50.480 --> 00:30:52.780
&gt;&gt; I don't know.

00:30:57.220 --> 00:30:59.020
&gt;&gt; Max Williamson: Okay, sure.

00:30:59.020 --> 00:31:11.040
[ Silence ]

00:31:11.040 --> 00:31:14.290
The language is structured
differently.

00:31:14.290 --> 00:31:18.390 position:56%
There are different grammatical
rules in everything than in English.

00:31:18.390 --> 00:31:22.820
So it does tend to start out with
the point and then it's explained.

00:31:22.820 --> 00:31:27.290
So what is the point,
expansion, talk about what it is,

00:31:27.290 --> 00:31:28.760
and then summarize the point.

00:31:28.760 --> 00:31:33.390
But in terms of comedy and poetry,
there are some very specific

00:31:33.390 --> 00:31:39.260
and idiosyncratic portions of that
that we can see that English has,

00:31:39.260 --> 00:31:42.550
but to interpret between
them is different.

00:31:42.550 --> 00:31:44.860
So the cultural part, understand

00:31:44.860 --> 00:31:49.420
that deaf typically are more
direct, blunt, and to the point.

00:31:49.420 --> 00:31:53.390
Whereas hearing try to kind of
obfuscate a little bit, maybe,

00:31:53.390 --> 00:31:56.380
you know, oh, skirt around
the question or the point.

00:31:56.380 --> 00:31:57.890
It's like, oh, a deaf
person said, wow,

00:31:57.890 --> 00:31:59.310
it looks like you've gained weight.

00:31:59.310 --> 00:32:03.320
You know, so there
could be that as well.

00:32:03.320 --> 00:32:04.860
Does that make sense?

00:32:04.860 --> 00:32:07.940
&gt;&gt; Yes. And I noticed the deaf
community here is very blunt

00:32:07.940 --> 00:32:09.740
and to the point.

00:32:09.740 --> 00:32:16.130
[ Silence ]

00:32:16.130 --> 00:32:18.430
&gt;&gt; Max Williamson: Yes.

00:32:23.370 --> 00:32:28.360
Yeah, and the point isn't
to insult or to be rude.

00:32:28.360 --> 00:32:32.870
It's just to, it doesn't
offend us, it's just kind of.

00:32:32.870 --> 00:32:35.560
In the deaf community when we
socialize with hearing people,

00:32:35.560 --> 00:32:39.110
they'll look at us like, whoa, that
was way too blunt, way too direct.

00:32:39.110 --> 00:32:41.400
But it's really just part of our
culture in how we communicate

00:32:41.400 --> 00:32:43.700
and interact with each other.

00:32:45.560 --> 00:32:50.160
Hearing people, they understand
me totally fine or with the things

00:32:50.160 --> 00:32:52.890 position:56%
