00:33:25.640 --> 00:33:29.650
And why do we cherish the language?

00:33:29.650 --> 00:33:33.540
I think before let's back up for a
little bit and talk about a child

00:33:33.540 --> 00:33:37.230
that is born deaf to
hearing parents.

00:33:37.230 --> 00:33:39.530
They don't have sign language.

00:33:40.770 --> 00:33:45.270
So they're obviously going
to be on a language delay.

00:33:51.090 --> 00:33:55.530
And we want these deaf children to
be able to acquire their language.

00:33:55.530 --> 00:33:58.880
That's why they have to start
signing at an early age.

00:34:00.200 --> 00:34:02.990
We had mentioned that there
was the new law that was passed

00:34:02.990 --> 00:34:05.580
that immediately out of
hospital, a baby has to go

00:34:05.580 --> 00:34:09.070
through a hearing test, and they
will be screened for hearing.

00:34:09.070 --> 00:34:11.810
That way they can find what is
the best modality to expose them

00:34:11.810 --> 00:34:14.750
to language at an early age.

00:34:14.750 --> 00:34:18.760
Often, hearing parents,
they have hearing children.

00:34:18.760 --> 00:34:21.060
It's not a problem.

00:34:23.050 --> 00:34:25.990
Hearing children have
language acquisition

00:34:25.990 --> 00:34:27.390
because of their hearing
parents, and they're able

00:34:27.390 --> 00:34:29.410
to share the same language.

00:34:29.410 --> 00:34:31.760
You know, if they don't
understand something, they can cry.

00:34:31.760 --> 00:34:34.690
The hearing parents are able to
realize that there is some type

00:34:34.690 --> 00:34:37.650
of communication with them.

00:34:37.650 --> 00:34:40.960 position:56%
We have started to see that they're
signing, hearing parents are signing

00:34:40.960 --> 00:34:42.400
with their hearing babies.

00:34:42.400 --> 00:34:43.700
Some of the basic signs.

00:34:43.700 --> 00:34:45.000
Because they're seeing

00:34:45.000 --> 00:34:47.690
that communication can
happen easier that way.

00:34:47.690 --> 00:34:49.630
So it's another reason
why we cherish and want

00:34:49.630 --> 00:34:51.930
to preserve our language.

